“ That whereas the Deane and Chapiter of tha Oathedrall Ghurche of Christe and blessed Marie the virgine of Durham consistinge ot twelve prebendaries, were and are lawfully seazed in their demeane as of fea as in the right ot their said churche, ot and in diverse and several] tenements and ferme- holds, in the severall tenuras and occupac’ons ot your said oratore lyinge and heinge in Ferrye Hill and manye other townees and hamletts in the countie of Durham, and they soo beinge ot the said severall tenements and fermeholds saazed‚ the said Deane and Prcbendaries myndeinge to made a lote- ment to everye one of them in severaltie ot a severall porc’on of the said possessione, so as everye oi them might mak a singulte and private profett to thern selvas, everyc of them of their seuerall portion so allotted, two yeres and a half sence or there abouts did conclud and agree emongest thern salves, that all the tenemento pareell of there possession being numbered ahud be putt into several] hillae or bylletta which in the whole

did amount to the numbre ot eight tenements for everye pre- bendarie and sexten for the Deane, and that everye one of them shuld in turne drawe their billctt till the bole by turne were drawen and that everye one of thern shuld hold in severaltie suche tenements as by loot shuld fall unto them by the same loterie and he to have and enioye the same severally for his most commoditie‚ which lootes being drawen everya ot' the said prebendes had eight several] tenements and the Deane sextene tenements, which tenements so alloted were in the several] tenures and occupac'ons of your said poore oratore and had contynewed in them and their auncestors tyme out ol man’s remembrance, aooordinge to tha laudable custome of tenuant right used there tyme owt of mynde, payingc ther at the change of everye tenuant two pennce and their rents and services aoenstomed, and servinge the Quene's Majestie and her noble progenitore upon the borders ot Skotland at the burneinge ot the Bekou, or upon comaundment from the Lord

Warden, with horse and man upon their owne charges by the

space of fiftene dales, at everye tyme aooordinge to the laudable

use and custome of tennant right their used.'’
